President Obama praises Senators Schumer and Graham for producing a bipartisan immigration reform framework. He believes that their proposal addresses the need to strengthen border security and hold both undocumented workers and employers accountable. The President plans to consult with the Senators on the details of their proposal and hopes that Congress will act quickly to turn it into legislation. He congratulates Senators Schumer and Graham for their leadership and pledges to work towards a bipartisan consensus on immigration reform this year.